  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nReport a bug.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\nWhen alternating between inline styles `{ borderLeft: '1px solid white' }` and a merge of it with\r\n`{ borderColor: 'red' }`, the white border is painted at the first render but a black border is painted\r\nwhen the `borderColor: 'red'` property is removed:\r\n\r\n![jul-16-2018 13-44-43](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1611639/42782668-6d325300-88fe-11e8-809b-04248e7f087c.gif)\r\n\r\n**Stackblitz example:**\r\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/react-dofznv\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\nGoing back to white border, just like the first render.\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\n\r\n- React 16.1.1 and 15.x.\r\n- macOS\r\n- Google Chrome, Safari\r\n",
